4:
I hear the Cobra's been active
again. A caravan was hit just this
morning...
6:
I thought that group of bandits was
destroyed long ago. Maybe that's
not true?
8:
It doesn't matter who's behind this.
We just have to be careful we're not
the next targets.
14:
So you're saying... You want to go
see whether the Cobra is still alive?
18:
You went back there by yourself? A
little reckless, don't you think?
23:
Hm? There's not much risk involved
with a little recon mission. I made it
back unscathed, didn't I?
25:
...There have always been rumors
like that floating around, but this
time the people aren't talking about
me.
28:
We parted ways so long ago... And,
well, I know there's no hope
anymore.
31: Still, I just want to be sure.
35:
Okay. We'll go with you, then. Right,
Nimbus?
40:
...Hmph. You're a pain in the ass, all
right. You don't watch your
surroundings in battle and can't be
relied upon for much.
45:
Didn't you JUST tell me to not go
back alone? If you don't want to
come, don't!
51:
Just a little further. The Cobra used
this abandoned village in the dunes
up ahead as a hideout.
54:
...There was a rule to leave a mark at
the hideout if you managed to
survive.
58:
...Is this your first time ever going
back?
65:
Speaking of which, I have managed
to survive. I wonder why I never
returned...
69:
...Wow, the nostalgia... It was always
so noisy here.
77:
I don't see any marks here... Looks
like that rumor was nothing to get
excited about.
80:
But somehow, I get the feeling that
people are still coming and going
through here...
88: Hmph... So that's what's going on.
93:
I can see you bastards sneaking
around over there!
97:
The silver-haired woman... The
Cobra's predecessor, are you?
Guess you're not as dead as the
rumors suggested.
100:
Predecessor? The hell does that
mean?
103:
Names are crazy things. Adopt the
right one, and rumors spread like
wildfire.
105:
I took on the name of the Cobra,
but... Well, I wasn't expecting the old
Cobra to still be alive.
107:
So we've gotta clear up the
confusion and bring the number of
Cobras back to one, got it?
110:
There's only one person to whom
that name belongs.
113:
Back off, you two. I'll take care of
them all myself.
122: Shut up... I need to handle this.
131:
We didn't come all the way out here
for you to reject our help!
136:
Yesterday's sun sets in the
sandstorm.
140:
The morning sun of tomorrow, too,
must also give way to night.
141:
But rely on your companions, and
the sunset will burn in your heart
forevermore.
143: Ahaha... What does that mean, Pops?
144: Hm? Only a poem I made just now.
146:
Pharah. When your friends have
your back, never hesitate to trust
them.
147:
Even if I'm not around... Don't reject
happiness.
150:
Pharah... Never reject happiness.
Find it, take hold, and never let go.
You'll remember that for me, won't
you?
152:
You understand what I'm telling you,
right?
164:
Don't reject it, huh... Was that really
all he said?
167:
Alk, Nimbus. You've got my back,
right?
181: Of course we've got your back!
